              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " 143Nd(2)O(3) were 4.077 and 3.875 mg/cm2 thick for",
                "  forward (0-90 deg) and backward (90-180 deg) alpha",
                "  events, respectively, and the diameter of both",
                "  samples was 10.8 cm.",
                " The backings of the samples were 0.005 inch thick",
                "  aluminum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " BF3 long counter as a neutron flux monitor"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The twin gridded ionization chamber,",
                "  comprised of two symmetric sections with common",
                "  cathode.",
                " The outer wall of the chamber was an aluminum",
                "  cylinder, 29.0 x 37.0 cm in height and diameter,",
                "  with 2.0 mm thick walls.",
                " The cathode, grids, and anodes were rectangular.",
                " The grids consisted of parallel tungsten wires,",
                "  coated with gold, which were 0.10 mm in diameter",
                "  and spaced 2.0 mm apart.",
                " The effective grid area was 16 x 18 cm2.",
                " Distances from the cathode to grid and from the grid",
                "  to anode were 75 and 20 mm, respectively.",
                " A mixture of Kr+2.89% CO2 was used as the working gas",
                "  for the ionization chamber.",
                " A gas pressure is 1.90 atm for present measurement.",
                " The high voltages for the cathode, grid and anode",
                "  were -3000, 0 and 1500 V, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron flux determination"
              ]
            }
          ],
